@endnode

@node Description
 DESCRIPTION
 ~~~~~~~~~~~

 Cookie is a door program to be used with the BBS program Max's BBS by
Anthony Barrett. 
 Cookie, as the name says, displays messages called cookies. These messages
are usually silly things, but can also be instructive bits of history ect.
The users will see one message on each login. The messages are chosen
randomly from a text file that you can create yourself or just find on the
nets.

 Features
 ````````

 Cookie can load only up to 2500 lines of text, but that should be enough
for most people :-)
 When you register this door, you will receive a text file with some of the
Murphy's laws either in English or Italian. I already have the Italian one,
and I'm looking for the English, and any other language, ones.
@endnode

@node Install
 INSTALLATION
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~

 To install the program you need to:
 1- Copy the Cookie directory in your Doors assigned directory. The program
    will look for its files there.
 
 2- Create a file called MainDoor.text containing the following line:
 	Cookie/Cookie
    
    Put this file in your Doors assigned directory. This file will call
    Cookie every time a user logs on. 
    
 3- Create a file in your Doors:Cookie/ directory containing the following
    text:
	line 1- Text displayed when the user is asked to press a key to
	        continue	
	line 2- #
	line 3- First line of the "cookie" text
	line 4- Second line of the "cookie" text
	.......
    After each "cookie" you must put a line containing only the #
    character. This separates the "cookies".
    
    For an example, give a look to the Cookie.text file that came in the
    archive.
    
 4- Change your startup-sequence or user-startup to add an assignement for
    Doors: to the directory where you put all your doors.   
	
 I know that all this seems long and maybe hard, but it was necessary in
order to let the sysops configure this door to their needs. It actually
takes only a few moments.
@endnode

